http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/Traffic-Metro-restrictions/article14012705.ece

Several restrictions on vehicle movements and some on the Delhi Metro will be imposed for the Republic Day full-dress rehearsal scheduled for Saturday.Metro services will be available at all stations on Friday, but no boarding and de-boarding will be allowed at Central Secretariat and Udyog Bhawan from 5 a.m. till noon on Friday. Similar restrictions will be imposed at Race Course and Patel Chowk from 8.45 a.m. to 12 noon.No traffic will be allowed from Vijay Chowk to India Gate on Rajpath from 6 p.m. on Friday until the parade is over the next day, said Joint CP (Traffic) Sharad Agarwal.